Definition of personal data
The PIPL defines personal data as any kind of information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person, either electronically or otherwise recorded, but excluding information that has been anonymized.
Definition of sensitive personal data
The PIPL defines sensitive personal data as information that, once leaked or illegally used, will easily lead to infringement of human dignity or harm to the personal or property safety of a natural person, including (but not limited to): (i) biometric data; (ii) religion; (iii) specific social status; (iv) medical health information; (v) financial accounts; (vi) tracking/location information; and (vii) minors data.&nbsp;Last modified 27 Jan 2022
				
			